From: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jun 2022 21:20:39 -0700
Subject: net: tun: unlink NAPI from device on destruction
Git-commit: 3b9bc84d311104906d2b4995a9a02d7b7ddab2db
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc5
References: CVE-2022-49672 bsc#1238816

Syzbot found a race between tun file and device destruction.
NAPIs live in struct tun_file which can get destroyed before
the netdev so we have to del them explicitly. The current
code is missing deleting the NAPI if the queue was detached
first.

Fixes: 943170998b20 ("tun: enable NAPI for TUN/TAP driver")
Reported-by: syzbot+b75c138e9286ac742647@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20220623042039.2274708-1-kuba@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Pedro Falcato <pfalcato@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/tun.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/tun.c b/drivers/net/tun.c
index 87a635aac008..7fd0288c3789 100644
--- a/drivers/net/tun.c
+++ b/drivers/net/tun.c
@@ -727,6 +727,7 @@ static void tun_detach_all(struct net_device *dev)
 		sock_put(&tfile->sk);
 	}
 	list_for_each_entry_safe(tfile, tmp, &tun->disabled, next) {
+		tun_napi_del(tfile);
 		tun_enable_queue(tfile);
 		tun_queue_purge(tfile);
 		xdp_rxq_info_unreg(&tfile->xdp_rxq);

